content.text:
The GitHub MCP provides these tools:

## Repository Management
- `search_repositories` - Search for GitHub repositories
- `create_repository` - Create new repository in your account
- `fork_repository` - Fork repository to your account/organization

## File Operations
- `get_file_contents` - Get contents of files/directories
- `create_or_update_file` - Create/update single file
- `push_files` - Push multiple files in single commit

## Branch Management
- `create_branch` - Create new branch
- `list_commits` - Get commit history

## Issues
- `list_issues` - List issues with filtering
- `get_issue` - Get specific issue details
- `create_issue` - Create new issue
- `update_issue` - Update existing issue
- `add_issue_comment` - Comment on issue

## Pull Requests
- `list_pull_requests` - List/filter PRs
- `get_pull_request` - Get PR details
- `create_pull_request` - Create new PR
- `get_pull_request_files` - List changed files
- `get_pull_request_status` - Check status/CI
- `get_pull_request_comments` - Get review comments
- `get_pull_request_reviews` - Get reviews
- `create_pull_request_review` - Create review with comments
- `merge_pull_request` - Merge PR
- `update_pull_request_branch` - Update with base branch

## Search
- `search_code` - Search code across repositories  
- `search_issues` - Search issues/PRs
- `search_users` - Search GitHub users

All operations support pagination and filtering where applicable.
